{{Infobox video game |title = Casey Powell Lacrosse 16 |image = |caption = |developer = [[Big Ant Studios]] |publisher = Crosse Studios |series = |released = March 9, 2016<ref name="laxvideogame.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.laxvideogame.com/lacrosse15/|title=Lacrosse 16 Official Site|publisher=laxvideogame.com|accessdate=29 February 2016}}</ref> |genre = [[Sports game|Sports]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]] }}
'''''Casey Powell Lacrosse 16''''' is a [[field lacrosse]] [[Simulation video game|simulation]] [[video game]] developed by [[Big Ant Studios]] and published by Crosse Studios for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]] that was released on March 9, 2016.<ref name="http://www.insidelacrosse.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.insidelacrosse.com/article/casey-powell-lacrosse-16-video-game-set-for-march-release/34092 |title=Casey Powell Lacrosse 16 Video Game Set For March Release |work=Inside Lacrosse |date=February 29, 2016}}</ref> [[Casey Powell]] was a star lacrosse player at [[Syracuse University]] and in [[Major League Lacrosse]].
Community Share has allowed for over 50 collegiate lacrosse teams and more than 9 pro lacrosse teams and developer-created teams.
